WEBVTT

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

01:06.399 --> 01:08.234
You two must have looked
inside the test room.

01:08.318 --> 01:09.444
Did it have a clock?

01:09.527 --> 01:10.445
It didn't.

01:11.237 --> 01:13.448
I'm sure they'll tell you the time,
but just in case,

01:13.531 --> 01:15.742
make sure you two bring watches.

01:15.825 --> 01:19.204
I'll pick you up at 7:00 a.m. tomorrow,
so come to the bus stop.

01:19.287 --> 01:21.664
-Don't be late.
-Okay.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.334
Go to bed early,

01:24.417 --> 01:27.087
make sure you eat breakfast,
and don't forget your packed lunch.

01:27.170 --> 01:29.464
And your exam ID slip. That's crucial.

01:29.547 --> 01:30.548
-Yes, sir.
-Okay.

01:31.841 --> 01:33.426
-Get a good night's sleep.
-Okay.

01:39.933 --> 01:40.850
Hello?

01:44.145 --> 01:46.564
Well, that…

01:47.148 --> 01:48.942
You mean the paperwork?

01:49.859 --> 01:51.945
<i>Let's meet at 6:50 a.m. tomorrow.</i>

01:52.028 --> 01:53.363
If you go in the room…

01:53.947 --> 01:55.281
The second drawer on the right.

01:55.365 --> 01:56.741
<i>Okay. Sleep tight.</i>

01:57.408 --> 01:58.868
It's there? I told you.

01:58.952 --> 02:00.787
Okay, I got it.

02:01.371 --> 02:03.123
Okay, bye.

02:10.463 --> 02:11.756
You didn't have to wait outside.

02:11.840 --> 02:13.508
Hello, Mr. Mu.

02:14.050 --> 02:16.052
You've gone above and beyond to help

02:16.136 --> 02:18.763
right up until the day before the exam.

02:18.847 --> 02:21.266
-We're really grateful.
-Not at all.

02:21.349 --> 02:22.642
It's my pleasure.

02:24.269 --> 02:28.231
Sir, Tae-seo needs a wristwatch,
but mine's digital.

02:28.314 --> 02:29.482
Do you have an analog one?

02:30.733 --> 02:33.027
This one's over 40 years old.

02:33.111 --> 02:34.445
It's fine as long as it works.

02:35.822 --> 02:36.781
Is that so?

02:38.449 --> 02:39.576
Give me your hand.

02:40.326 --> 02:41.286
Put it on now,

02:41.369 --> 02:42.412
so you don't forget.

02:50.753 --> 02:53.214
You two did a great job looking after him.

02:54.382 --> 02:56.009
You did far more for him.

03:47.894 --> 03:48.937
<i>Did you sleep well?</i>

03:49.020 --> 03:51.272
Yeah, better than I thought I would.

03:51.356 --> 03:52.982
I thought I'd be too nervous to sleep.

03:53.566 --> 03:56.402
I think knowing you'd be taking
the exam in the next room

03:56.486 --> 03:57.695
made me feel at ease.

04:00.782 --> 04:02.909
Did you wait long? You must've been cold.

04:03.785 --> 04:04.744
I'm hot.

04:04.827 --> 04:07.413
My dad said it's always cold
in Korea on exam day.

04:10.166 --> 04:11.084
I want to wear it.

04:20.802 --> 04:21.844
Like this?

04:21.928 --> 04:22.762
No.

04:26.474 --> 04:29.310
Wrap it round and around,

04:30.728 --> 04:31.729
and then tie it.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.410
My goal is to get into a school
as close to you as possible.

04:46.286 --> 04:48.830
If I can't get into one in Seoul,
then at least one nearby.

04:52.000 --> 04:55.086
Please let us both
achieve our goals today.

04:57.005 --> 04:58.006
I think

04:58.715 --> 05:00.300
this will help me do well.

05:01.467 --> 05:02.635
Give me something too.

05:02.719 --> 05:03.636
Anything of yours.

05:13.021 --> 05:13.855
I have something.

05:16.441 --> 05:18.568
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

05:19.193 --> 05:20.028
My lucky charm.

05:22.488 --> 05:26.034
EXAM ROOM 6

05:44.385 --> 05:50.308
STILL SHINING

05:51.684 --> 05:54.353
The exam's over!

05:57.607 --> 05:58.608
Am I the only happy one?

06:02.737 --> 06:03.613
It's over!

06:07.116 --> 06:09.410
Tae-seo, let's go see the Hangang River.

06:09.494 --> 06:11.287
We've seen the ocean,
so we need to go there.

06:11.954 --> 06:13.039
But the time…

06:13.122 --> 06:14.248
Come on. We can make it.

06:15.750 --> 06:16.793
One second.

06:24.842 --> 06:25.927
I only have 7,000 won.

06:26.469 --> 06:27.386
Let's go next time.

06:32.183 --> 06:34.435
I didn't use my allowance
since I was studying with you.

06:34.519 --> 06:36.771
You helped me save it,
so I should spend it with you.

06:36.854 --> 06:38.356
Come on, let's take the train.

06:46.364 --> 06:47.615
Not the train.

06:58.042 --> 07:00.169
Let's see the river
from Dongseoul Bus Terminal.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.462
Can you see it from there?

07:01.546 --> 07:03.840
Yeah, the Hangang River is close
to Gangbyeon Station.

07:05.049 --> 07:07.301
We'll see the river,
leave from Gangbyeon Station,

07:07.385 --> 07:10.555
take the last train from Cheongnyangni,
and arrive early tomorrow morning.

07:10.638 --> 07:12.014
Why are we taking the train back?

07:12.557 --> 07:15.393
The train takes around six hours…

07:18.062 --> 07:21.357
so we can be together for longer.

07:23.484 --> 07:24.360
Genius.

07:27.738 --> 07:29.699
What can we do with 7,000 won?

07:31.409 --> 07:32.827
Buy me noodles from a tent bar.

07:32.910 --> 07:35.413
My dad said the noodles
in Seoul tent bars are really good.

07:36.706 --> 07:37.540
Okay.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.887
-Want to go there?
-Okay.

07:52.430 --> 07:53.764
Here are your noodles.

07:53.848 --> 07:55.016
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

08:03.483 --> 08:04.942
It's familiar, but it's delicious.

08:09.989 --> 08:11.866
I love noodles.

08:11.949 --> 08:13.868
And every time, my dad would say

08:13.951 --> 08:15.495
that when my mom was pregnant with me,

08:15.578 --> 08:17.121
she'd always crave these noodles.

08:17.663 --> 08:19.790
I'd always wondered what they tasted like.

08:25.463 --> 08:26.672
I know.

08:26.756 --> 08:28.966
I'm always talking
about my mom when I come to Seoul.

08:29.050 --> 08:30.259
I don't miss her though.

08:33.596 --> 08:34.430
Does she live here?

08:35.723 --> 08:36.849
No, she lives abroad.

08:37.850 --> 08:39.143
But I don't know where.

08:39.227 --> 08:40.561
I never asked.

08:42.230 --> 08:44.065
I'm sure she's doing well somewhere.

08:45.566 --> 08:47.693
Somewhere that has nothing to do with me.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.575
We can take the subway
at 10:00 p.m., so don't rush.

08:55.701 --> 08:56.953
What about the Hangang River?

08:57.995 --> 08:59.580
You can see it from the station.

08:59.664 --> 09:00.957
Not from the station.

09:01.040 --> 09:02.833
I want to see it up close.

09:07.713 --> 09:08.631
We better eat quickly.

09:15.805 --> 09:17.848
The Hangang River's right in front of me.

09:17.932 --> 09:18.933
This is my first time.

09:19.016 --> 09:19.892
Me too.

09:20.685 --> 09:22.853
-Let's get a bit closer.
-Wait.

09:24.814 --> 09:25.856
You're…

09:26.607 --> 09:27.525
going to be cold.

09:29.402 --> 09:30.319
Wrap it round…

09:31.988 --> 09:32.989
and around,

09:33.573 --> 09:34.448
and then tie it.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.870
What about you? Aren't you cold?

09:39.954 --> 09:40.788
I can…

09:42.707 --> 09:43.666
just wear this.

09:57.513 --> 09:58.556
It's a historic day.

09:58.639 --> 10:00.600
I saw both the ocean
and the Hangang River.

10:01.851 --> 10:03.311
I have to remember this day.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.277
Yeon Tae-seo.

10:11.360 --> 10:13.404
I just found my dream.

10:13.487 --> 10:14.447
Living on my own.

10:15.072 --> 10:16.407
Living away from my dad.

10:16.490 --> 10:18.993
This counts as a dream

10:19.076 --> 10:21.495
because it's only possible
if my dad gets better.

10:21.579 --> 10:23.998
If he's not doing well,
I can't even consider it.

10:24.081 --> 10:27.460
My dream is for my dad to get well
so I can become independent.

10:29.462 --> 10:30.296
How about you?

10:31.380 --> 10:32.381
Me?

10:33.132 --> 10:34.258
Mine is…

10:37.178 --> 10:39.388
If yours is independence,
mine is self-reliance.

10:40.056 --> 10:41.307
I don't have a "from."

10:42.725 --> 10:44.060
That's really amazing.

10:44.810 --> 10:45.645
What do you mean?

10:45.728 --> 10:48.898
Because I know
you'll achieve that like it's nothing.

10:49.482 --> 10:52.234
From what I've seen,
you're good at doing things on your own.

10:53.486 --> 10:55.696
-I am?
-Yeah.

10:55.780 --> 10:57.615
I don't like doing things by myself,

10:57.698 --> 10:59.158
but you're really good at it.

10:59.241 --> 11:01.786
I've never seen you hang out with people.

11:02.370 --> 11:03.663
You're fine on your own.

11:04.288 --> 11:05.498
It's kind of amazing.

11:06.957 --> 11:08.084
Then again,

11:08.167 --> 11:10.461
I bet things will be different
when you go to college.

11:12.088 --> 11:14.632
I wonder what else will change about you.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.511
I doubt anything will change.

11:23.099 --> 11:24.100
Want to go a bit further?

11:25.851 --> 11:27.728
Yeah. Do we have time?

11:31.774 --> 11:33.484
No, we don't.

11:35.778 --> 11:36.612
Let's go.

11:37.696 --> 11:38.531
We have to go.

11:38.614 --> 11:39.907
Come on, we'll be late.

11:52.002 --> 11:53.838
We walked way too far to see the river.

11:57.174 --> 11:58.175
Hold on.

11:59.301 --> 12:00.302
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

12:00.845 --> 12:02.012
I burned off all the noodles.

12:05.433 --> 12:06.600
Come on, we're late.

12:10.229 --> 12:11.230
Let's go.

12:17.319 --> 12:18.320
Run.

12:43.262 --> 12:46.807
<i>This morning at the bus stop,</i>

12:47.349 --> 12:48.851
<i>I was watching you arrive.</i>

13:07.036 --> 13:08.579
<i>Where we'll be,</i>

13:09.497 --> 13:10.539
<i>what we'll be doing,</i>

13:11.332 --> 13:12.458
<i>and with whom.</i>

13:14.001 --> 13:17.880
<i>I wondered which of these three</i>
<i>would be decided by today's exam.</i>

13:20.090 --> 13:20.925
<i>Then,</i>

13:21.717 --> 13:24.970
<i>could this be the last time</i>

13:25.554 --> 13:27.014
<i>we're headed</i>

13:28.641 --> 13:29.975
<i>in the same direction?</i>

13:33.437 --> 13:35.064
It's not certain yet,

13:35.981 --> 13:38.817
but things will change
when we're at different schools, right?

13:40.611 --> 13:41.654
No.

13:42.363 --> 13:45.699
Distance only mattered
when text messages didn't exist.

13:48.452 --> 13:50.538
If we can still send texts,

13:51.205 --> 13:52.414
no place is too far.

13:53.332 --> 13:54.708
We can text from anywhere.

13:54.792 --> 13:56.085
Exactly.

13:57.253 --> 13:58.629
Texting works everywhere.

13:59.255 --> 14:00.798
Even Yeonwoo has great service.

14:02.049 --> 14:05.761
Would texting not work somewhere
really remote in another country?

14:05.844 --> 14:07.596
Unless we're in different worlds,

14:09.181 --> 14:10.391
we can still text.

14:11.976 --> 14:13.143
Different worlds…

14:15.271 --> 14:16.522
That's my mom and me.

14:19.984 --> 14:20.859
Same.

14:25.072 --> 14:27.491
There's something that only applies to us.

14:29.201 --> 14:30.536
Because it's you and me.

14:32.621 --> 14:37.501
You and I are going to try really hard
to spend time together.

14:39.378 --> 14:41.171
We'll make every effort.

14:45.676 --> 14:47.678
You like me that much?

14:49.054 --> 14:50.055
Of course.

14:50.639 --> 14:52.641
If I hadn't been this sure,

14:54.685 --> 14:56.061
I wouldn't have even tried.

14:57.354 --> 14:58.397
Even when I had…

15:00.900 --> 15:03.986
no room in my life to like someone,
these feelings still grew.

16:48.465 --> 16:49.758
I want to be with you.

17:12.239 --> 17:13.782
-Shall we?
-Yeah.

17:14.283 --> 17:15.284
Shall we?

18:05.459 --> 18:06.585
Where should I go?

18:09.505 --> 18:10.589
Over there?

19:22.995 --> 19:24.788
Your room is nice.

19:25.706 --> 19:26.665
Yeah.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.017
Let me…

19:45.601 --> 19:46.602
I can do it.

20:58.173 --> 20:59.007
Hold on.

21:35.002 --> 21:36.003
Sorry.

22:21.381 --> 22:22.466
Eun-a, are you home?

22:30.807 --> 22:31.975
Is that your dad?

22:33.643 --> 22:34.728
Eun-a.

22:34.811 --> 22:36.271
Yeah, Dad!

22:42.444 --> 22:43.612
I'm home.

22:45.113 --> 22:46.656
I'm going to wash up and go to bed.

22:46.740 --> 22:48.241
Are you going to school tomorrow?

22:48.325 --> 22:49.868
I have to, but I can go late.

22:51.453 --> 22:52.454
Good night, Dad.

22:53.371 --> 22:54.748
Okay, well done today.

22:55.290 --> 22:56.291
Get some rest.

22:57.084 --> 22:58.293
I'm proud of you, my girl.

22:59.127 --> 23:00.087
Thanks.

23:16.103 --> 23:17.062
Is he gone?

23:56.059 --> 23:57.060
No.

24:01.690 --> 24:04.276
Actually, I have a huge secret.

24:06.278 --> 24:08.780
I was too embarrassed to tell you.

24:25.005 --> 24:26.715
I was so hot I thought I'd die.

24:27.924 --> 24:30.218
I kept thinking about my thermals
as I took off my coat.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.888
It wasn't even that cold today,
but my dad insisted.

24:35.390 --> 24:36.683
This is so embarrassing.

24:36.766 --> 24:39.019
Why did it have to be floral?

24:41.897 --> 24:42.981
What?

24:44.149 --> 24:45.358
I think it's cute.

25:36.785 --> 25:38.870
You've always done well,

25:38.954 --> 25:40.497
so let's just figure out where to go.

25:40.580 --> 25:41.873
Go think about it.

25:41.957 --> 25:43.625
Okay. Thank you.

25:43.708 --> 25:44.668
Off you go.

25:49.214 --> 25:50.340
My gosh.

26:09.484 --> 26:11.861
Mo Eun-a, well done. You did a good job.

26:12.821 --> 26:13.655
Thank you.

26:14.614 --> 26:18.159
You did really well considering
you only started studying half a year ago.

26:19.160 --> 26:19.995
Really.

26:20.495 --> 26:22.163
If you'd started a year earlier,

26:23.081 --> 26:25.000
we could've tried
the regional admissions track.

26:25.583 --> 26:26.584
It's a shame.

26:28.420 --> 26:29.963
Now, let's see.

27:06.124 --> 27:11.880
DECEMBER

27:19.554 --> 27:21.431
DEPARTMENT OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERING

27:21.514 --> 27:23.016
YOUR APPLICATION HAS BEEN SUBMITTED

27:23.099 --> 27:24.309
All done.

27:24.392 --> 27:26.561
I feel so glad
to have it submitted quickly.

27:27.395 --> 27:30.148
The results come out on February 4th, so…

27:30.231 --> 27:31.983
Just kick back and relax.

27:42.994 --> 27:44.788
Yeah, it's beautiful.

28:03.640 --> 28:04.682
Eun-a.

28:09.979 --> 28:11.981
Merry early Christmas.

28:25.620 --> 28:26.621
The guests are here.

28:26.704 --> 28:28.373
Yeah, I'm all done.

28:30.041 --> 28:32.794
Thanks to your help,
I'm officially on the concierge team now.

28:32.877 --> 28:33.753
Thank you so much.

28:34.754 --> 28:37.507
I heard you specifically asked
to work with only me.

28:38.550 --> 28:39.551
Because you're good.

28:43.304 --> 28:46.224
I think having to deal with
a different person each time

28:46.891 --> 28:48.560
bothers Seon-gyu a bit.

28:48.643 --> 28:50.186
He seemed to struggle with it.

28:51.229 --> 28:52.856
So it's a win-win.

28:55.358 --> 28:57.110
You haven't had dinner yet, right?

28:57.193 --> 29:00.655
You eat this one,
and please take the other one to Eun-a.

29:02.532 --> 29:05.869
Whenever the guests are here,
she never comes out of her room.

29:11.332 --> 29:13.209
How did you feel when you submitted it?

29:13.293 --> 29:16.796
Mr. Mu did it for me.
He clicked the "Submit" button too.

29:16.880 --> 29:18.047
He clicked it for you?

29:18.715 --> 29:20.508
I didn't ask him to,

29:20.592 --> 29:22.302
but it was just easier for him to do it.

29:23.970 --> 29:25.930
I'd be too nervous to click it myself.

29:28.558 --> 29:31.352
Do adults always have to deal
with stressful things like this?

29:32.103 --> 29:34.522
Why am I always so nervous and scared?

30:09.015 --> 30:10.683
MY APPLICATIONS

30:18.817 --> 30:21.402
If you're done, I'll click it now.
I'm going to submit it.

30:21.486 --> 30:23.279
Mr. Mu, wait.

30:23.363 --> 30:26.241
-No, you've done more than enough.
-Please just wait.

30:26.324 --> 30:28.493
-I can't wait anymore.
-Wait, hold on!

30:28.576 --> 30:30.161
It's Christmas today.

30:30.245 --> 30:31.746
Can I just pray one time?

30:35.708 --> 30:36.960
I should get up to do it.

30:37.961 --> 30:39.045
It's okay. Just pray.

30:39.128 --> 30:41.506
-This gave me a bad feeling.
-Go on, just pray.

30:45.301 --> 30:47.262
Hopefully, we can make it home today.

30:49.764 --> 30:51.599
Dear Santa,
I really want to go to college.

30:51.683 --> 30:54.686
JANUARY

31:10.493 --> 31:11.953
Oh, my god!

31:13.037 --> 31:14.372
Why are you hiding in the corner?

31:14.956 --> 31:15.957
It's so dark.

31:16.916 --> 31:18.585
-You should've turned the lights on.
-No…

31:20.253 --> 31:21.462
I'm fine.

31:27.510 --> 31:28.636
Please come over here.

31:54.162 --> 31:56.915
One thing's for sure.
We always have plenty to eat at our house.

31:58.333 --> 31:59.500
Enjoy your meal.

32:01.669 --> 32:03.796
We need the one you just swiped tonight,

32:05.340 --> 32:06.591
so take any of these instead.

32:08.509 --> 32:09.510
Okay.

32:42.460 --> 32:43.920
Happy New Year.

33:29.340 --> 33:31.509
My first day as a 20-year-old
with Yeon Tae-seo.

33:37.181 --> 33:38.224
We don't have any glasses.

33:58.411 --> 33:59.245
It's sweet.

34:13.843 --> 34:14.969
It's pretty tasty.

34:18.639 --> 34:19.640
It's not alcohol.

34:19.724 --> 34:21.100
It is alcohol.

34:55.843 --> 34:57.095
Let's go.

35:29.669 --> 35:30.920
Eun-a!

35:32.922 --> 35:33.923
Be quiet.

35:42.014 --> 35:47.478
FEBRUARY

35:48.980 --> 35:51.691
All right, shall we toast?

35:53.317 --> 35:54.902
Congratulations.

35:55.862 --> 35:59.740
He made it to Hanguk National University
from this tiny village. Congratulations.

35:59.824 --> 36:01.868
You're too kind.

36:01.951 --> 36:04.078
It's all thanks to Mr. Mu here.

36:04.162 --> 36:06.414
I didn't do much.

36:06.497 --> 36:08.166
He achieved it all on his own.

36:08.249 --> 36:10.585
So did Mr. Mo's daughter not get in?

36:10.668 --> 36:12.044
No, she's still waiting.

36:12.128 --> 36:13.963
There's a first round of results,

36:14.046 --> 36:16.549
then a second, and even a third.

36:16.632 --> 36:18.259
The results come out in batches.

36:18.342 --> 36:20.386
So it's a little complicated.

36:20.469 --> 36:22.471
Gosh, you didn't have to.

36:22.555 --> 36:24.265
Have some of this, Mr. Mu.

36:24.348 --> 36:25.600
-Congratulations.
-Great job.

36:25.683 --> 36:27.059
Thank you.

36:27.143 --> 36:28.936
So, Mr. Mu.

36:29.020 --> 36:31.355
Explain it properly so I can understand.

36:31.439 --> 36:34.400
Well, there is
an additional enrollment period,

36:34.483 --> 36:38.988
and the results don't finish
coming out until late February.

36:39.071 --> 36:40.948
What on earth does that mean?

36:41.032 --> 36:43.784
It must be killing Eun-a
to wait for the results.

36:45.161 --> 36:46.037
Right.

36:52.501 --> 36:53.628
This is my first time.

36:54.545 --> 36:55.546
On the Sea Train?

36:56.714 --> 36:57.798
THIS IS THE SEA TRAIN

36:57.882 --> 37:01.385
It only runs during the day
and follows the coastline.

37:01.469 --> 37:04.472
It takes an hour and 40 minutes
from Gangneung to Samcheok,

37:04.555 --> 37:06.140
so if we go there and come back…

37:06.224 --> 37:08.893
We can be together
for around three and a half hours.

37:09.644 --> 37:10.645
Yeah.

37:14.357 --> 37:15.733
When I was little,

37:16.692 --> 37:18.778
my mom worked here for a bit.

37:20.029 --> 37:22.281
I wanted to become
a Sea Train driver back then.

37:23.491 --> 37:25.284
I guess it looked kind of cool.

37:28.496 --> 37:29.830
That's nice.

37:32.375 --> 37:34.418
What did you want to tell me
all the way out here?

37:41.592 --> 37:43.803
I have to go to Seoul soon.

37:45.471 --> 37:48.641
When I was living in Seoul,
I had a friend called Hyeong-seok.

37:48.724 --> 37:50.393
And his dad runs a study center.

37:51.644 --> 37:54.647
He let me use it for free
and helped me out a lot.

37:56.023 --> 37:58.401
He asked if I could do
some tutoring starting in February.

37:59.318 --> 38:00.820
I'd been putting it off,

38:01.904 --> 38:04.240
but I think I really have to go now.

38:08.744 --> 38:09.912
Right.

38:11.998 --> 38:12.832
You should go.

38:14.292 --> 38:15.543
And your entrance ceremony?

38:15.626 --> 38:17.086
Is Hui-seo joining you later?

38:17.670 --> 38:19.046
He can't go.

38:19.130 --> 38:20.840
He can't do long journeys yet.

38:21.382 --> 38:22.591
He must be upset.

38:24.176 --> 38:25.303
Do you have a place to stay?

38:25.386 --> 38:27.930
Yeah, the study center office has a bed.

38:28.014 --> 38:30.057
How can you sleep in an office?

38:32.268 --> 38:33.352
That's so sad.

38:35.104 --> 38:36.355
That's nothing.

38:38.024 --> 38:39.942
You must be more sad
waiting for your results.

38:42.695 --> 38:43.571
Me? Well…

38:44.238 --> 38:46.324
One of the three schools I applied to

38:46.907 --> 38:48.701
is at least close to you,

38:49.410 --> 38:51.454
but my chances of getting in are low.

38:51.537 --> 38:54.206
One is halfway between
here and Seoul, but it's not certain.

38:54.290 --> 38:56.542
The last one is in Gangneung.

38:57.960 --> 39:01.047
Mr. Mu said it's a good school,
and the program is good there.

39:02.256 --> 39:03.132
But…

39:04.342 --> 39:06.052
it's really far from you.

39:06.677 --> 39:10.848
Having to wait for over a month
is making me anxious and uncertain.

39:11.474 --> 39:13.309
It's been dragging on for so long

39:13.392 --> 39:15.353
that I can't believe
February is already ending.

39:15.895 --> 39:17.104
It feels endless.

39:26.530 --> 39:28.032
It's definitely going to end.

39:30.242 --> 39:31.952
I hope so.

39:40.336 --> 39:42.505
An end that really feels like one.

39:43.631 --> 39:45.716
I hope it's a clean end.

40:11.992 --> 40:12.952
Wait.

40:17.289 --> 40:19.417
This isn't much, but take it.

40:19.500 --> 40:21.001
I'm fine. I have money.

40:21.085 --> 40:22.795
Buy yourself something to wear.

40:24.463 --> 40:26.132
Your grandma seemed to feel bad

40:26.215 --> 40:28.884
we couldn't buy you something to wear

40:28.968 --> 40:31.053
to your entrance ceremony.

40:32.304 --> 40:34.390
We can't afford to buy you a suit,

40:34.473 --> 40:37.893
but at least buy yourself a coat.

40:37.977 --> 40:39.728
Something that's nice and formal.

40:40.479 --> 40:42.857
You'll need to dress up
quite often while in the city.

40:42.940 --> 40:45.067
Here. Buy one for yourself.

40:46.360 --> 40:47.528
Thank you.

40:49.822 --> 40:53.075
From scholarships to tutoring,
you're doing everything on your own.

40:53.159 --> 40:54.660
We feel terrible.

40:58.080 --> 40:58.998
I'll visit often.

41:00.332 --> 41:03.210
There's no need. You should be studying.
You'll only waste money.

41:04.587 --> 41:06.255
Just make sure you call Hui-seo.

41:09.341 --> 41:12.136
I thought he'd be grumpy
about missing your entrance ceremony,

41:12.845 --> 41:13.888
but he's been quiet.

41:18.684 --> 41:22.521
At least the ceremony doesn't fall
on the same day as your parents' memorial.

41:23.731 --> 41:25.107
It's the first one.

41:32.531 --> 41:34.325
I'll go pay my respects.

41:35.284 --> 41:36.619
Stay at home with Hui-seo.

41:41.790 --> 41:42.750
All right.

41:43.667 --> 41:44.960
Go on, then.

41:45.878 --> 41:46.712
Okay.

41:53.385 --> 41:59.183
WAITING AREA (TICKETS)

42:02.436 --> 42:05.272
<i>Are you taking the express bus to Seoul?</i>

42:06.690 --> 42:07.525
Eun-a.

42:10.736 --> 42:13.322
I was waiting right here.

42:13.405 --> 42:15.407
I thought you'd be taking the train.

42:15.491 --> 42:16.450
I'm such a klutz.

42:18.160 --> 42:19.370
I just…

42:19.453 --> 42:22.456
I know you told me not to,
but I'd feel bad if I didn't see you off.

42:22.540 --> 42:25.709
I'll take you there.
I bought two tickets, so we can just go.

42:25.793 --> 42:26.919
Don't be ridiculous.

42:40.558 --> 42:42.810
How can you make me let you go home alone?

42:43.686 --> 42:44.853
You can let it happen today.

42:51.402 --> 42:52.820
Seriously, it's fine.

42:56.115 --> 42:57.533
Let's get off at the next stop.

42:58.534 --> 43:01.620
I can't bear to watch you go back alone.
I'll take you home and…

43:01.704 --> 43:03.247
So you can go alone, but I can't?

43:04.915 --> 43:06.750
That's nonsense. It's fine.

43:09.962 --> 43:11.630
It's already been an hour.

43:11.714 --> 43:13.132
We don't have time.

43:13.215 --> 43:14.967
How long are you going to keep this up?

43:25.769 --> 43:28.063
LOG IN

43:31.108 --> 43:33.277
PLAYLIST

43:35.738 --> 43:36.655
This is my account.

43:37.573 --> 43:41.577
If I'm using it, it'll say,
"Currently streaming."

43:42.328 --> 43:44.747
We can use it together.
We'll listen to it at the same time.

43:45.414 --> 43:46.415
Then,

43:47.458 --> 43:49.710
it'll feel like we're together.

43:51.837 --> 43:53.714
It'll feel like we're together.

43:53.797 --> 43:54.882
Feeling like we're together

43:56.258 --> 43:57.426
counts as being together.

44:01.305 --> 44:02.306
I like that.

44:02.973 --> 44:04.433
What else is there

44:04.516 --> 44:06.101
to make us feel together?

44:07.811 --> 44:10.481
Sharing the photos we take?
Let's take one now.

44:14.068 --> 44:14.902
Smile.

44:22.826 --> 44:25.162
Sir, how long will it take?

44:25.245 --> 44:26.163
One hour.

44:26.246 --> 44:27.081
What?

44:30.959 --> 44:33.545
You should go.
Let's part here. It's your first lesson.

44:34.463 --> 44:35.422
Eun-a.

44:38.384 --> 44:40.135
This is a lot

44:40.719 --> 44:42.096
harder than I expected.

44:43.180 --> 44:44.431
I can't do it.

44:45.307 --> 44:46.392
I can.

44:46.475 --> 44:49.436
Come on, I can't let you go back alone.

44:50.896 --> 44:53.107
You can. Just like this.

44:53.190 --> 44:56.735
I might end up at a college near you,
or I might not.

44:57.444 --> 44:58.987
I don't know what will happen.

45:00.781 --> 45:02.032
My life is always so uncertain.

45:03.784 --> 45:05.661
Anyway, we'll have to keep doing this,

45:05.744 --> 45:08.247
but if you feel bad or guilty,
it'll be hard to see each other.

45:12.793 --> 45:13.794
This is driving me crazy.

45:16.964 --> 45:18.048
I'll…

45:18.715 --> 45:20.050
I'll do my best for us.

45:20.884 --> 45:21.802
Okay.

45:28.767 --> 45:29.643
Oh, my god.

45:30.769 --> 45:31.770
What?

45:31.854 --> 45:33.355
What is it?

45:33.439 --> 45:34.481
I got in.

45:35.107 --> 45:35.941
What?

45:36.525 --> 45:38.235
GANGNEUNG WONKYEONG UNIVERSITY

45:39.361 --> 45:41.113
No way! I got in!

45:41.196 --> 45:43.615
See? I got in because I was with you!

45:44.825 --> 45:47.077
Oh, my god. But it's a bit far from you.

45:47.161 --> 45:49.455
That's not what matters right now!

45:50.622 --> 45:52.416
Congratulations!

45:54.168 --> 45:57.588
-You really earned this.
-Oh, my god. I'm so happy.

45:57.671 --> 46:01.717
MARCH

46:47.596 --> 46:49.389
-It's nice.
-Nice and clean.

46:49.473 --> 46:50.807
You must be his roommate.

46:50.891 --> 46:52.434
I hope you two get along well.

46:53.143 --> 46:56.271
-The bed here's so soft.
-Sweetie, don't sit there.

46:56.355 --> 46:58.357
Why not? Come try it too, Mom.

47:01.902 --> 47:02.986
This is nice.

47:15.749 --> 47:16.833
Hui-seo…

47:19.169 --> 47:21.338
I'll bring him over when he's a bit older.

47:29.137 --> 47:30.931
Don't worry about him.

47:34.643 --> 47:37.104
And don't worry about Grandma and Grandpa.

47:41.984 --> 47:43.777
I'll take care of everyone.

47:50.659 --> 47:51.660
I almost forgot.

47:53.912 --> 47:56.290
I'm attending the college
you wanted me to go to, Mom.

48:03.630 --> 48:05.716
You would've been so happy
to see me there.

48:13.724 --> 48:14.725
Mom.

48:17.394 --> 48:18.270
Dad.

48:58.977 --> 49:00.771
Can I sit here?

49:00.854 --> 49:01.813
Sure.

49:12.532 --> 49:13.659
I'm Park Na-ri.

49:15.285 --> 49:16.203
I'm Mo Eun-a.

49:18.205 --> 49:20.707
Hey, your student number
is right after mine.

49:21.416 --> 49:22.417
What a coincidence.

49:24.670 --> 49:26.672
I'm from Seoul. You?

49:26.755 --> 49:28.965
I live nearby. Twenty minutes by bus.

49:29.049 --> 49:30.217
-Twenty minutes?
-Yeah.

49:36.431 --> 49:38.100
No way! We have the same elective too?

49:38.183 --> 49:40.352
No way! Come sit here.

49:47.818 --> 49:48.735
What's that?

49:52.698 --> 49:55.409
-Want to pick one?
-They're so cute.

49:56.618 --> 49:57.869
-This one.
-Sure.

49:57.953 --> 49:59.663
-Here.
-Thanks.

50:00.914 --> 50:05.585
This class is called
Creative Engineering Design.

50:05.669 --> 50:07.295
This class will give you the opportunity

50:07.379 --> 50:10.882
to reflect on what lies
beyond the machines.

50:10.966 --> 50:12.926
Great machines are made
when you understand

50:13.009 --> 50:14.261
both their function and value.

50:14.344 --> 50:17.973
What you need for this class
is your mathematical ability

50:18.056 --> 50:19.808
and a brain that's capable of thinking.

50:19.891 --> 50:22.853
The rest you will learn
in this class today.

50:24.062 --> 50:26.314
Did you always want to study
early childhood education?

50:26.398 --> 50:28.692
Yeah, because I like kids.

50:30.193 --> 50:33.655
But teaching's not really for me.
It's not what I expected.

50:35.532 --> 50:38.493
I picked this place for the major,
but now, I'm not so sure.

50:41.496 --> 50:43.540
But it's so nice to see the ocean.

50:44.875 --> 50:46.752
This was worth skipping class.

50:46.835 --> 50:47.669
I know.

50:49.755 --> 50:51.798
I heard the vending machine coffee
was good here.

50:51.882 --> 50:54.259
SORI MARKET

50:54.342 --> 50:55.385
-Want to go?
-Let's go.

50:58.388 --> 50:59.765
<i>We're already really close.</i>

50:59.848 --> 51:01.391
<i>I'm exploring Gangneung thanks to her.</i>

51:01.475 --> 51:03.477
I'll take you around
the next time you're here.

51:03.560 --> 51:04.895
Okay.

51:07.314 --> 51:09.524
<i>I have matching stickers with Na-ri,</i>

51:09.608 --> 51:11.735
<i>but I don't have</i>
<i>anything matching with you.</i>

51:14.613 --> 51:15.864
What do you want to do?

51:17.657 --> 51:19.409
I have a great idea.

51:19.493 --> 51:21.912
What if I make stickers with my drawings?

51:21.995 --> 51:24.206
<i>The same vegetable stickers</i>
<i>for our different classes.</i>

51:24.790 --> 51:25.832
<i>Tell me your classes.</i>

51:25.916 --> 51:27.584
I'll draw something for each one.

51:27.667 --> 51:28.585
I'm really good.

51:30.337 --> 51:31.546
Engineering Mathematics.

51:32.297 --> 51:33.131
<i>Kidney beans.</i>

51:33.215 --> 51:34.800
It's extremely hard to pick them out.

51:36.551 --> 51:39.763
They're hard to pick out? Then…

51:39.846 --> 51:40.972
APRIL

51:43.600 --> 51:45.185
-Kim Na-rae.
-Here.

51:47.062 --> 51:48.230
Kim Ji-ho.

51:49.731 --> 51:50.690
Ji-ho?

51:52.234 --> 51:53.985
-Mo Eun-a.
-Here.

51:55.612 --> 51:56.613
Park Na-ri.

51:57.739 --> 51:59.324
Right, Na-ri took a leave of absence.

52:00.492 --> 52:04.079
It's only been a month,
and someone's already taking time off.

52:06.122 --> 52:08.208
-Park Seo-yeon.
-Here.

52:08.291 --> 52:10.293
-Song A-yeong.
-Here.

52:21.304 --> 52:22.472
PLAYLIST

52:31.523 --> 52:33.525
TAE-SEO

52:33.608 --> 52:35.652
<i>Have the flowers bloomed in Seoul yet?</i>

52:35.735 --> 52:37.237
<i>It's crazy here.</i>

52:37.320 --> 52:39.447
<i>Send me a photo</i>
<i>of the flowers at your school too.</i>

52:39.531 --> 52:43.118
<i>And a selfie of you in front of them too.</i>

52:47.289 --> 52:49.624
<i>I miss you, Tae-seo.</i>

52:50.792 --> 52:52.836
-Hello.
-Hello.

53:05.765 --> 53:08.393
<i>I'll go to school after tutoring</i>
<i>and send it to you.</i>

53:23.158 --> 53:26.494
His tutoring session usually takes
about two hours, so…

53:28.413 --> 53:30.624
<i>Call me when you're done tutoring, okay?</i>

53:49.309 --> 53:50.894
<i>What time do you finish?</i>

53:51.770 --> 53:53.563
WHAT TIME DO YOU FINISH?

54:01.988 --> 54:03.823
<i>I have two tutoring sessions today,</i>

54:03.907 --> 54:05.617
<i>so if I go straight to school after,</i>

54:05.700 --> 54:06.910
<i>it should be around 10:00 p.m.</i>

54:16.711 --> 54:18.421
One ticket to Gangneung, please.

54:19.172 --> 54:20.298
Gangneung?

54:21.007 --> 54:22.217
That'll be 10,600 won.

54:26.805 --> 54:27.639
Dad.

54:29.766 --> 54:31.059
You never ask me to pick you up.

54:31.810 --> 54:32.852
I didn't want to go alone.

54:33.853 --> 54:35.814
Are we going out for a night stroll?

54:35.897 --> 54:38.024
Where should we go? Let's go for sashimi.

54:39.985 --> 54:41.027
I'm tired.

54:55.709 --> 54:57.502
What should we eat?

54:57.585 --> 54:59.587
Is there something you'd like to eat?

55:00.505 --> 55:01.881
I'm up for anything.

55:03.133 --> 55:04.175
Should we ask Eun-a?

55:04.259 --> 55:06.386
Eun-a, is there anything you want to eat?

55:07.595 --> 55:08.763
Eun-a, are you asleep?

55:10.598 --> 55:12.017
She must be really tired.

55:12.100 --> 55:13.685
Just let her sleep.

55:15.103 --> 55:16.855
But we haven't gone out
together in forever.

55:17.480 --> 55:19.441
It'd be nice if we could talk while we go.

55:19.524 --> 55:21.151
<i>I had no idea they'd bloomed so much.</i>

55:22.610 --> 55:23.611
<i>Should I call you?</i>

55:24.195 --> 55:25.321
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

55:26.656 --> 55:29.200
<i>I was just wandering and thought of you.</i>

55:30.785 --> 55:33.788
<i>I can leave in the morning this weekend.</i>

55:33.872 --> 55:34.831
<i>Let's meet up early.</i>

55:35.790 --> 55:37.208
<i>I want to go to Seoul.</i>

55:38.168 --> 55:39.461
<i>It's my turn to go.</i>

55:39.544 --> 55:40.795
<i>I'll come to you.</i>

55:40.879 --> 55:42.380
<i>No, I'll go to you.</i>

55:42.922 --> 55:44.340
<i>Spend your time on yourself.</i>

55:44.424 --> 55:45.759
<i>Don't waste it.</i>

55:45.842 --> 55:47.469
Hello, Hyeong-seok? Yeah.

55:48.136 --> 55:49.929
<i>Your time is precious too.</i>

55:50.013 --> 55:50.972
<i>I'll go to you.</i>

55:55.643 --> 55:57.896
<i>My time right now is just passing by,</i>

55:58.772 --> 56:02.108
<i>but yours is time you need to use</i>
<i>toward your goals.</i>

56:02.192 --> 56:03.318
<i>They're different.</i>

56:05.612 --> 56:07.280
<i>No more dark photos.</i>

56:08.323 --> 56:10.075
<i>I miss you, Tae-seo.</i>

56:11.242 --> 56:12.285
<i>A lot.</i>

57:08.007 --> 57:08.967
This is nice.

57:09.050 --> 57:10.260
Did you miss me?

57:12.262 --> 57:13.096
Of course.

57:16.391 --> 57:23.356
MAY

57:39.205 --> 57:41.583
Every time I take out a cigarette,
you appear.

57:41.666 --> 57:42.709
It's almost scary.

57:46.796 --> 57:48.590
It's fun working at a hotel, isn't it?

57:49.340 --> 57:51.384
I feel good
whenever I see the hotel staff.

57:51.468 --> 57:52.844
Then, try it out.

57:53.344 --> 57:55.638
A lot of local young people
work part-time at our hotel.

57:55.722 --> 57:56.973
Taking time off from school?

57:58.349 --> 57:59.809
What would I be taking time off for?

57:59.893 --> 58:01.686
I don't want to try things out
without a goal

58:01.769 --> 58:03.688
just because everyone else is.

58:04.814 --> 58:05.773
So annoying.

58:07.609 --> 58:09.861
I mean, I know you're in college,

58:09.944 --> 58:12.322
but it's not even vacation time
and you're not at school.

58:12.405 --> 58:15.325
You've been here all day today
and riding your bike the past two days.

58:16.075 --> 58:17.202
You're the first one to ask.

58:17.785 --> 58:19.787
I skipped school all week and slacked off,

58:19.871 --> 58:20.955
but no one's ever asked.

58:21.039 --> 58:22.832
No one from school reached out.

58:22.916 --> 58:25.126
And my dad didn't ask why I wasn't going.

58:25.960 --> 58:27.462
I guess no one really cares.

58:28.046 --> 58:29.631
Thanks for asking.

58:30.173 --> 58:32.675
I'm not going to school
because I don't feel like going.

58:32.759 --> 58:34.677
If you're going to
do college half-heartedly,

58:34.761 --> 58:37.180
you might as well take time off
and try something else.

58:37.263 --> 58:38.640
Don't you want to be independent?

58:39.265 --> 58:40.808
In your current situation,

58:40.892 --> 58:43.144
I doubt your dad would notice
you're not going to school.

58:43.228 --> 58:45.355
If I were you,
I'd be thinking about moving out.

58:49.359 --> 58:51.694
That came out of nowhere. What situation?

58:51.778 --> 58:53.696
Just go pick up your guests.

58:53.780 --> 58:56.866
It was a lunch reservation,
but it'll be dinner time soon.

58:58.034 --> 59:00.537
So-hyeon made
a surprise announcement today.

59:00.620 --> 59:02.622
I can't really ruin the mood.

59:03.289 --> 59:04.582
Announcement?

59:05.583 --> 59:08.294
-You two look great together.
-I'm so happy for you.

59:08.378 --> 59:09.671
Congratulations.

59:09.754 --> 59:11.130
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

59:11.214 --> 59:12.131
Congratulations.

59:12.215 --> 59:14.133
-I'll bring out some more wine.
-All right.

59:16.970 --> 59:18.054
Cheers.

59:25.103 --> 59:26.396
You're here just in time.

59:26.479 --> 59:28.314
Your dad announced
they're getting married.

59:28.398 --> 59:29.649
You should congratulate them.

59:53.214 --> 59:54.424
What about the Unit 610 guy?

59:55.633 --> 59:56.884
It took you long enough to ask.

59:58.011 --> 59:59.262
I'll end things with him.

59:59.345 --> 01:00:00.763
You're only ending it now?

01:00:01.931 --> 01:00:03.808
Seon-gyu knows everything.

01:00:04.726 --> 01:00:07.103
He said he'd tell me
once he figured things out,

01:00:07.186 --> 01:00:08.896
so I hadn't been able to end things.

01:00:11.065 --> 01:00:11.899
Eun-a.

01:00:11.983 --> 01:00:16.654
Love doesn't happen in perfect order.

01:00:16.738 --> 01:00:18.906
No wonder why
you always have a guy around.

01:00:18.990 --> 01:00:20.325
There's never a break with you.

01:00:20.408 --> 01:00:22.368
-Watch what you say.
-You watch it.

01:00:22.452 --> 01:00:23.953
How dare you two-time my dad?

01:00:28.333 --> 01:00:30.001
Seon-gyu is the one I have feelings for.

01:00:30.084 --> 01:00:31.628
The one in Unit 610 knows that too.

01:00:31.711 --> 01:00:34.339
I've never deceived or misled anyone.

01:00:34.422 --> 01:00:36.716
So you're saying you'll live
however you want

01:00:36.799 --> 01:00:38.718
and everyone else
has to just deal with it?

01:00:39.927 --> 01:00:42.055
And my dad just accepted that nonsense?

01:00:44.682 --> 01:00:46.184
What do you take my dad for?

01:00:47.226 --> 01:00:49.812
He's a good person, but someone like you…

01:00:49.896 --> 01:00:50.813
This is the last time.

01:00:50.897 --> 01:00:52.815
I'll let your insults slide today,

01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:54.150
but after this,

01:00:54.942 --> 01:00:56.110
not a chance.

01:01:01.449 --> 01:01:02.283
Mo Eun-a.

01:01:05.244 --> 01:01:06.287
Mo Eun-a!

01:01:07.205 --> 01:01:08.039
Let go.

01:01:08.956 --> 01:01:10.249
You should congratulate them.

01:01:10.333 --> 01:01:12.085
You're startling our guests.

01:01:12.168 --> 01:01:13.628
Take this and go back inside.

01:01:13.711 --> 01:01:15.463
You're so damn good at your job.

01:01:19.759 --> 01:01:23.137
Aren't you a little old to be so worked up
over your dad's relationship?

01:01:24.305 --> 01:01:26.015
You should focus on your own life.

01:01:27.684 --> 01:01:28.851
I'll try to find you a job.

01:01:31.729 --> 01:01:33.106
I can't promise it'll help though.

01:02:30.913 --> 01:02:33.666
It tends to stop or flip over
on steep inclines.

01:02:34.584 --> 01:02:36.461
Could the weight distribution be off?

01:02:36.544 --> 01:02:38.379
How about switching to a two-wheel design?

01:02:38.463 --> 01:02:39.881
<i>Are you busy?</i>

01:02:39.964 --> 01:02:41.174
<i>I'm in my professor's lab.</i>

01:02:41.257 --> 01:02:43.134
<i>It's only for grad students,</i>

01:02:43.217 --> 01:02:45.511
<i>but the TA let me in,</i>
<i>so it's my first time here.</i>

01:02:45.595 --> 01:02:46.554
<i>It's pretty cool.</i>

01:02:47.138 --> 01:02:49.932
<i>You sound busy. What time do you finish?</i>

01:02:50.016 --> 01:02:53.603
<i>What is it? If it's urgent,</i>
<i>I can call you right now.</i>

01:02:53.686 --> 01:02:55.938
You should be majoring in flattery.

01:02:56.939 --> 01:02:59.233
Honestly. We'll continue this in a bit.

01:02:59.317 --> 01:03:01.736
<i>-Never mind. I'll catch you later.</i>
-Yes, Professor.

01:03:02.487 --> 01:03:04.906
The professor likes supreme pizza.

01:03:04.989 --> 01:03:07.200
-Could I go use the restroom?
-Yeah, sure.

01:03:08.534 --> 01:03:09.827
Professor, please have some.

01:03:14.040 --> 01:03:15.500
<i>Did you know?</i>

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:19.462
<i>Apparently, you can see Namsan</i>
<i>from anywhere in Seoul.</i>

01:03:19.545 --> 01:03:22.882
<i>So from now on, your name is Namsan.</i>

01:03:22.965 --> 01:03:24.175
<i>Yeon Namsan.</i>

01:03:26.636 --> 01:03:29.931
<i>I guess I'm still stuck in uncertainty.</i>

01:03:38.523 --> 01:03:39.607
<i>Where are you?</i>

01:03:40.691 --> 01:03:42.068
<i>The wetlands.</i>

01:03:42.151 --> 01:03:45.279
<i>No. I'm actually at the bus stop now.</i>

01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:51.786
TAE-SEO

01:03:58.292 --> 01:03:59.252
<i>You're in Seoul, right?</i>

01:04:00.878 --> 01:04:03.172
<i>While I was wandering,</i>
<i>I was going to buy some makeup</i>

01:04:03.256 --> 01:04:05.466
<i>and get a bowl of noodles.</i>

01:04:06.175 --> 01:04:08.052
<i>You have important things going on.</i>

01:04:08.135 --> 01:04:09.554
<i>Don't waste your time.</i>

01:04:09.637 --> 01:04:12.640
<i>I have plenty of time,</i>
<i>so I'll drop by again.</i>

01:04:13.558 --> 01:04:15.309
<i>Don't be ridiculous.</i>

01:04:15.393 --> 01:04:17.311
<i>Nothing matters more</i>
<i>than us being together.</i>

01:04:24.110 --> 01:04:27.446
<i>Tae-seo, I really want to see you.</i>

01:04:34.287 --> 01:04:35.246
<i>I'm on my way.</i>

01:04:36.080 --> 01:04:37.415
<i>You don't know where I am.</i>

01:04:38.791 --> 01:04:39.625
<i>Hang on.</i>

01:04:47.800 --> 01:04:48.968
<i>I have one more stop.</i>

01:04:49.051 --> 01:04:49.886
<i>I'm almost there.</i>

01:05:01.856 --> 01:05:03.316
GANGBYEON STATION

01:05:13.659 --> 01:05:16.829
<i>I can hear Yeon Tae-seo coming.</i>

01:05:27.506 --> 01:05:29.300
<i>I'm done wandering.</i>

01:05:32.303 --> 01:05:35.222
STILL SHINING

01:06:01.165 --> 01:06:04.085
<i>You were really going through it</i>
<i>before you did your military duty.</i>

01:06:04.794 --> 01:06:06.337
<i>I hate goodbyes.</i>

01:06:07.254 --> 01:06:08.756
For 10 years, I'd forgotten.

01:06:09.966 --> 01:06:11.300
<i>They were gone.</i>

01:06:11.384 --> 01:06:13.094
Eun-a…

01:06:13.177 --> 01:06:15.054
You haven't heard from her, have you?

01:06:15.763 --> 01:06:16.973
<i>Let's stop…</i>

01:06:18.265 --> 01:06:20.059
<i>with the worries and everything else.</i>

01:06:20.142 --> 01:06:21.352
<i>I thought of you.</i>

01:06:24.563 --> 01:06:27.274
<i>I had hoped to see you at least once.</i>

01:06:34.323 --> 01:06:36.325
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
